result.formatted_address: 8 Shelter St, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Sonata

reviews.text:
There is semi buffet lunch here 108 +10%, very good price in a causeway bay hotel.
The main dishes taste ok not very good.
There are some appetizers and dessert which taste good

This place was good since it is in a Hotel, Rosedale Hotel. But, personally, the food was not so good bcs not many choices as the menu as served for buffet, lunch buffet. And, the servant is nice, they gonna asking you about the taste of the food. Overall, everything is fine.  You could try this.

I mean, what can you expect for lunch buffet at $118 near Causeway Bay. There are plenty of different foods from western and Chinese.  Don't expect the food to be Michelin quality but they definitely will fill your stomach. The bread pudding was quite good though and credits to the friendly staff!
Wonderful caring staff, elegant and delicious food, definately worth visiting!
reasonable price quick buffet lunch dont expect glamour but definitely can fill u up.

result.adr_address: 8 Shelter St, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 8 Shelter St, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Rosedale Hotel Hong Kong

reviews.text:
Check in was fast and smooth. The front desk staff was nice to give us an upgrade to a Suites room due to the high occupancy rates. Manager Anthony was pleasant, courteous and patient in answering our queries and providing personalized recommendations.

Lifts were rather slow and small and it took quite a while to reach our room/ the lobby. Room was spacious; albeit rather dated. The rooms could definitely use some upgrading in their furnishings. There was a nice view to the city skyline and harbor area too. Access to the mini bar was also complimentary for the first night.

Its proximity to the popular Causeway Bay shopping areas, Victoria Park, Central Library and many other food outlets was a plus point. Breakfast buffet was disappointingly mediocre. It was lacking in variety and average tasting. A complimentary shuttle, H3, is also provided on a regular basis for commuters to shuttle between the hotel and Hong Kong station.

I've been to the Rosedale Hotel located on the border of Causeway Bay and Victoria Park for tea on several occasions.

My cousins and my auntie took is there for tea several times whenever i visit Hong Kong.

Like most 4 stars hotels, the restaurant settings and the  cuisines are standard.  

The formula is bigger, better and good food.  

The tea settings was elegant and fancy.  Each guest had their own pot of tea.  

Service is always adequate and friendly at the Roaedake for afternoon tea.

Do visit Victoria Park if you are at the Rosedale Hotel  right across the street.
Quick.check in, room's fine,  breakfast more than sufficient; lifts take forever esp around check.out time and the lift stops on every floor.

Although it looks like an amazing hotel on the outside and entrance, the rooms are a bit dirty and smelly. Smells a lot like cigarettes. The rooms are also tiny. For the price is ok, but just don’t be fooled when you get there and see it at face value.
Room was fine, breakfast good, lifts are still incredibly slow so bring patience.

Terribile il servizio. Albergo vecchio e tenuto male. Scortesi alla reception. Camere sotto lo standard di decenza. Ha 5 stelle questo hotel? Nemmeno 2 stelle .
地點較近維多利亞公園和銅鑼灣，既方便購物又可到公園享受市中心式郊遊樂，還可到全港最大的圖書館中央圖書館參觀，借閱有聲與無聲圖書，很是寫意！
房間較小，設備老舊，整層樓都有股霉味，不過房間清潔還蠻到位的，早餐口味還不錯，但餐廳服務人員工作態度應可改善， 入座前請她幫忙擦桌子，竟然直接要我們換位子，然後群聚聊天，這就不太能接受了
